\int \frac{x^2}{x - 2} = \int x +\frac{4}{x-2} + 2  
\int \frac{x^2}{x - 2} 
\int x +\frac{4}{x-2} + 2  
 \frac{x^2}{x - 2} = \frac{x^2 - 2x + 2x}{x - 2} = x + \frac{2x}{x - 2} 
 \frac{2x}{x - 2} = \frac{ 2x - 4 + 4 }{ x - 2 } = 2 + \frac{4}{x - 2} 
x^2 = (x^2 - 4x + 4) + 4x - 4 = (x-2)^2 + 4x-4
4x - 4 = 4(x-2) + 8 - 4 = 4(x-2) + 4
x^2 = (x-2)^2 + 4(x-2) + 4
